UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Charles F. COCO, Appellee. No. 7763. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 5, 1935. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., of Los Angeles, Cal., for the United States. James H. O’Neill and Wm. H. Wilson, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges. .

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed: mandate forthwith.
